   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solar Project Saves Lives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Mwandi Hospital, a designated COVID center in Western Province Zambia, requires reliable, low-cost electrical power in order to provide quality patient care. Costs charged by the national hydroelectric power company (ZESCO) are increasing exponentially. Our project&apos;s long-term goal is to remove the hospital from the ZESCO power grid by installing a sustainable solar power system. The hospital will apply its cost-savings directly to patient care and its health-care services will be expanded.</narrative>
  </description>
